meteor.module.description.air-jump: Lets you jump in the air.
meteor.module.description.air-place: Places a block where your crosshair is pointing at.
meteor.module.description.ambience: Change the color of various pieces of the environment.
meteor.module.description.anchor: Helps you get into holes by stopping your movement completely over a hole.
meteor.module.description.anchor-aura: Automatically places and breaks Respawn Anchors to harm entities.
meteor.module.description.anti-afk: Performs different actions to prevent getting kicked while AFK.
meteor.module.description.anti-anvil: Automatically prevents Auto Anvil by placing between you and the anvil.
meteor.module.description.anti-bed: Places string to prevent beds being placed on you.
meteor.module.description.anti-packet-ki: Attempts to prevent you from being disconnected by large packets.
meteor.module.description.anti-void: Attempts to prevent you from falling into the void.
meteor.module.description.arrow-dodge: Tries to dodge arrows coming at you.
meteor.module.description.attribute-swap: Swaps to a target slot when you attack.
meteor.module.description.auto-anvil: Automatically places anvils above players to destroy helmets.
meteor.module.description.auto-city: Automatically mine blocks next to someone's feet.
meteor.module.description.auto-exp: Automatically repairs your armor and tools in pvp.
meteor.module.description.auto-log: Automatically disconnects you when certain requirements are met.
meteor.module.description.auto-mend: Automatically replaces items in your offhand with mending when fully repaired.
meteor.module.description.auto-nametag: Automatically uses nametags on entities without a nametag. WILL nametag ALL entities in the specified distance.
meteor.module.description.auto-reconnect: Automatically reconnects when disconnected from a server.
meteor.module.description.auto-replenish: Automatically refills items in your hotbar, main hand, or offhand.
meteor.module.description.auto-sign: Automatically writes signs. The first sign's text will be used.
meteor.module.description.auto-smelter: Automatically smelts items from your inventory
meteor.module.description.auto-tool: Automatically switches to the most effective tool when performing an action.
meteor.module.description.auto-totem: Automatically equips a totem in your offhand.
meteor.module.description.auto-trap: Traps people in a box to prevent them from moving.
meteor.module.description.auto-wasp: Wasps for you. Unable to traverse around blocks, assumes a clear straight line to the target.
meteor.module.description.auto-weapon: Finds the best weapon to use in your hotbar.
meteor.module.description.auto-web: Automatically places webs on other players.
meteor.module.description.bed-aura: Automatically places and explodes beds in the Nether and End.
meteor.module.description.better-beacons: Select effects unaffected by beacon level.
meteor.module.description.better-chat: Improves your chat experience in various ways.
meteor.module.description.better-tab: Various improvements to the tab list.
meteor.module.description.better-tooltip: Displays more useful tooltips for certain items.
meteor.module.description.blink: Allows you to essentially teleport while suspending motion updates.
meteor.module.description.block-selectio: Modifies how your block selection is rendered.
meteor.module.description.blur: Blurs background when in GUI screens.
meteor.module.description.boss-stack: Stacks boss bars to make your HUD less cluttered.
meteor.module.description.bow-aimbot: Automatically aims your bow for you.
meteor.module.description.breadcrumbs: Displays a trail behind where you have walked.
meteor.module.description.break-delay: Changes the delay between breaking blocks.
meteor.module.description.break-indicato: Renders the progress of a block being broken.
meteor.module.description.build-height: Allows you to interact with objects at the build limit.
meteor.module.description.burrow: Attempts to clip you into a block.
meteor.module.description.camera-tweaks: Allows modification of the third person camera.
meteor.module.description.chest-swap: Automatically swaps between a chestplate and an elytra.
meteor.module.description.city-esp: Displays blocks that can be broken in order to city another player.
meteor.module.description.click-tp: Teleports you to the block you click on.
meteor.module.description.collisions: Adds collision boxes to certain blocks/areas.
meteor.module.description.criticals: Performs critical attacks when you hit your target.
meteor.module.description.discord-presen: Displays Meteor as your presence on Discord.
meteor.module.description.echest-farmer: Places and breaks EChests to farm obsidian.
meteor.module.description.elytra-boost: Boosts your elytra as if you used a firework.
meteor.module.description.elytra-fly: Gives you more control over your elytra.
meteor.module.description.enderman-look: Either looks at all Endermen or prevents you from looking at Endermen.
meteor.module.description.entity-control: Lets you control rideable entities without a saddle.
meteor.module.description.entity-owner: Displays the name of the player who owns the entity you're looking at.
meteor.module.description.exp-thrower: Automatically throws XP bottles from your hotbar.
meteor.module.description.fake-player: Spawns a client-side fake player for testing usages. No need to be active.
meteor.module.description.fast-use: Allows you to use items at very high speeds.
meteor.module.description.flamethrower: Ignites every alive piece of food.
meteor.module.description.flight: FLYYYY! No Fall is recommended with this module.
meteor.module.description.free-look: Allows more rotation options in third person.
meteor.module.description.freecam: Allows the camera to move away from the player.
meteor.module.description.gui-move: Allows you to perform various actions while in GUIs.
meteor.module.description.hand-view: Alters the way items are rendered in your hands.
meteor.module.description.high-jump: Makes you jump higher than normal.
meteor.module.description.hole-esp: Displays holes that you will take less damage in.
meteor.module.description.instant-rebrea: Instantly re-breaks blocks in the same position.
meteor.module.description.item-highlight: Highlights selected items when in guis
meteor.module.description.item-physics: Applies physics to items on the ground.
meteor.module.description.jesus: Walk on liquids and powder snow like Jesus.
meteor.module.description.light-overlay: Shows blocks where mobs can spawn.
meteor.module.description.liquid-filler: Places blocks inside of liquid source blocks within range of you.
meteor.module.description.liquid-interac: Allows you to interact with liquids.
meteor.module.description.logout-spots: Displays a box where another player has logged out at.
meteor.module.description.long-jump: Allows you to jump further than normal.
meteor.module.description.marker: Renders shapes. Useful for large scale projects
meteor.module.description.message-aura: Sends a specified message to any player that enters render distance.
meteor.module.description.middle-click-e: Perform various actions when you middle click.
meteor.module.description.mount-bypass: Allows you to bypass the IllegalStacks plugin and put chests on entities.
meteor.module.description.multitask: Lets you use items and attack at the same time.
meteor.module.description.nametags: Displays customizable nametags above players, items and other entities.
meteor.module.description.no-fall: Attempts to prevent you from taking fall damage.
meteor.module.description.no-ghost-block: Attempts to prevent ghost blocks arising.
meteor.module.description.no-interact: Blocks interactions with certain types of inputs.
meteor.module.description.no-mining-trac: Allows you to mine blocks through entities.
meteor.module.description.no-render: Disables certain animations or overlays from rendering.
meteor.module.description.no-rotate: Attempts to block rotations sent from server to client.
meteor.module.description.no-slow: Allows you to move normally when using objects that will slow you.
meteor.module.description.offhand: Allows you to hold specified items in your offhand.
meteor.module.description.offhand-crash: An exploit that can crash other players by swapping back and forth between your main hand and offhand.
meteor.module.description.packet-cancell: Allows you to cancel certain packets.
meteor.module.description.packet-logger: Allows you to log certain packets.
meteor.module.description.packet-mine: Sends packets to mine blocks without the mining animation.
meteor.module.description.parkour: Automatically jumps at the edges of blocks.
meteor.module.description.pop-chams: Renders a ghost where players pop totem.
meteor.module.description.portals: Allows you to use GUIs normally while in a Nether Portal.
meteor.module.description.potion-saver: Stops potion effects ticking when you stand still.
meteor.module.description.reverse-step: Allows you to fall down blocks at a greater speed.
meteor.module.description.safe-walk: Prevents you from walking off blocks.
meteor.module.description.self-anvil: Automatically places an anvil on you to prevent other players from going into your hole.
meteor.module.description.server-spoof: Spoof client brand, resource pack and channels.
meteor.module.description.slippy: Changes the base friction level of blocks.
meteor.module.description.speed: Modifies your movement speed when moving on the ground.
meteor.module.description.speed-mine: Allows you to quickly mine blocks.
meteor.module.description.spider: Allows you to climb walls like a spider.
meteor.module.description.stash-finder: Searches loaded chunks for storage blocks. Saves to <your minecraft folder>/meteor-client
meteor.module.description.step: Allows you to walk up full blocks instantly.
meteor.module.description.surround: Surrounds you in blocks to prevent massive crystal damage.
meteor.module.description.swarm: Allows you to control multiple instances of Meteor from one central host.
meteor.module.description.time-changer: Makes you able to set a custom time.
meteor.module.description.timer: Changes the speed of everything in your game.
meteor.module.description.tracers: Displays tracer lines to specified entities.
meteor.module.description.trail: Renders a customizable trail behind your player.
meteor.module.description.trajectories: Predicts the trajectory of throwable items.
meteor.module.description.trident-boost: Boosts you when using riptide with a trident.
meteor.module.description.vein-miner: Mines all nearby blocks with this type
meteor.module.description.velocity: Prevents you from being moved by external forces.
meteor.module.description.void-esp: Renders holes in bedrock layers that lead to the void.
meteor.module.description.xray: Only renders specified blocks. Good for mining.
meteor.setting.description.border: Space around the edges of the screen.
meteor.setting.description.category-icon: Adds item icons to module categories.
meteor.setting.description.chat-feedback: Sends chat feedback when meteor performs certain actions.
meteor.setting.description.custom-window: Show custom text in the window title.
meteor.setting.description.delete-chat-f: Delete previous matching chat feedback to keep chat clear.
meteor.setting.description.friend-color: The color used to show friends.
meteor.setting.description.hidden-module: Prevent these modules from being rendered as options in the clickgui.
meteor.setting.description.hide-in-menus: Hides the meteor hud when in inventory screens or game menus.
meteor.setting.description.logged-in-tex: Color of logged in account name.
meteor.setting.description.module-backgr: Color of module background when active.
meteor.setting.description.module-search: Amount of modules and settings to be shown in the module search bar.
meteor.setting.description.prune-by-late: Prune proxies at or above this latency in ms. 0 to disable.
meteor.setting.description.prune-to-coun: If in excess, prune the number of proxies to this count. 0 to disable. Prioritises by latency.
meteor.setting.description.retries-on-ti: How many additional times to check a proxy if the check times out.
meteor.setting.description.rotation-hold: Hold long to hold server side rotation when not sending any packets.
meteor.setting.description.search-module: Whether or not module aliases will be used in the module search bar.
meteor.setting.description.sort-by-laten: Whether to sort the proxy list by latency.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-ac: Color of accessed objects (before a dot) in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-br: Color of braces in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-co: Color of commas in starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-do: Color of dots in starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-ke: Color of keywords in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-nu: Color of numbers in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-op: Color of operators in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-pa: Color of parenthesis in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-st: Color of strings in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.starscript-te: Color of text in Starscript code.
meteor.setting.description.sync-list-set: Prevents the list setting screens from moving around as you add & remove elements.
meteor.setting.description.text-colors: Colors used for the Text element.
meteor.setting.description.text-scale: Scale of text if not overridden by the element.
meteor.setting.description.threads: The number of concurrent threads to check proxies with.
meteor.setting.description.timeout: The timeout in milliseconds for checking proxies.
meteor.setting.description.title-screen-: Show Meteor credits on title screen
Show Meteor splash texts on title screen
meteor.setting.description.use-team-colo: Uses player's team color for rendering things like esp and tracers.
meteor.setting.description.window-title-: The text it displays in the window title.
